The paper deals with machine learning and interpretable classification rules, which are topics that fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of Conjunctive Normal Form (CNF) and MaxSAT solvers, which are techniques used in the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed framework in real-world instances, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
